{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3550894,"name":"","username":"Wing","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/wing/{size}/175245_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-08T02:07:21.476Z","cooked":"<p>We used 6328’s drive to pose command as a template for our own alignment and we got the logic to work pretty well while we were using the talon fx swerve template  but when i switched to ctre swervegen and tried to feed my x,y, and omega velocities to my drivetrain its pretty much completely off and really the only thing thats changed is how the velocities are passed through.</p>
<p>this is what the code looks like:</p>
<p>package frc.robot.commands.drive;</p>
<p>import edu.wpi.first.math.MathUtil;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.math.controller.ProfiledPIDController;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Pose2d;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Rotation2d;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Translation2d;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.math.kinematics.ChassisSpeeds;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.math.trajectory.TrapezoidProfile;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.smartdashboard.SmartDashboard;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.Command;<br>
import frc.robot.Constants;<br>
import frc.robot.subsystems.CommandSwerveDrivetrain;<br>
//import frc.robot.subsystems.drive.Drive;<br>
import frc.robot.util.GeomUtil;<br>
//import frc.robot.util.LoggedTunableNumber;<br>
import java.util.function.DoubleSupplier;<br>
import java.util.function.Supplier;<br>
//import org.littletonrobotics.junction.AutoLogOutput;<br>
//import org.littletonrobotics.junction.Logger;</p>
<p>import com.ctre.phoenix6.swerve.SwerveRequest;<br>
import com.ctre.phoenix6.swerve.SwerveModule.DriveRequestType;</p>
<p>public class DriveToPose extends Command {</p>
<p>private final CommandSwerveDrivetrain drivetrain;<br>
private final Supplier desiredPose;</p>
<p>private Translation2d lastSetpoint = new Translation2d();</p>
<p>private Supplier linearFF = () → Translation2d.kZero;<br>
private DoubleSupplier omegaFF = () → 0.0;</p>
<p>private double driveErrorAbs, thetaErrorAbs = 0;<br>
private double ff_minRadius = 0.05;<br>
private double ff_maxRadius = 0.1;</p>
<p>private boolean running = false;</p>
<p>/*  private static final LoggedTunableNumber drive_kP =<br>
new LoggedTunableNumber(“DriveToPose/driveKp”);<br>
private static final LoggedTunableNumber turn_kP = new LoggedTunableNumber(“DriveToPose/turnKp”);<br>
private static final LoggedTunableNumber ff_minRadius =<br>
new LoggedTunableNumber(“DriveToPose/minRadius”);<br>
private static final LoggedTunableNumber ff_maxRadius =<br>
new LoggedTunableNumber(“DriveToPose/maxRadius”); */</p>
<p>static {<br>
// drive_kP.initDefault(.5);<br>
// turn_kP.initDefault(.5);</p>
<pre><code>//ff_minRadius.initDefault(0.05);
//ff_maxRadius.initDefault(.1);
</code></pre>
<p>}</p>
<p>private final ProfiledPIDController driveController =<br>
new ProfiledPIDController(.5, 0.0, 0.0, new TrapezoidProfile.Constraints(.5, 1));<br>
private final ProfiledPIDController thetaController =<br>
new ProfiledPIDController(2, 0., 0.0, new TrapezoidProfile.Constraints(.5, 1));</p>
<p>public DriveToPose(CommandSwerveDrivetrain drivetrain, Supplier desiredPose) {<br>
this.drivetrain = drivetrain;<br>
this.desiredPose = desiredPose;</p>
<pre><code>thetaController.enableContinuousInput(-Math.PI, Math.PI);

addRequirements(drivetrain);
</code></pre>
<p>}</p>
<p><a class="mention" href="/u/override">@Override</a><br>
public void initialize() {<br>
drivetrain.setKillSwitch(false);<br>
Pose2d currentPose = drivetrain.getPose();</p>
<pre><code>ChassisSpeeds fieldVelocity = drivetrain.getFieldVelocity();
Translation2d linearFieldVelocity =
    new Translation2d(fieldVelocity.vxMetersPerSecond, fieldVelocity.vyMetersPerSecond);

driveController.reset(
    currentPose.getTranslation().getDistance(desiredPose.get().getTranslation()),
    Math.min(
        0,
        -linearFieldVelocity
            .rotateBy(
                desiredPose
                    .get()
                    .getTranslation()
                    .minus(currentPose.getTranslation())
                    .getAngle()
                    .unaryMinus())
            .getX()));

thetaController.reset(
    currentPose.getRotation().getRadians(), fieldVelocity.omegaRadiansPerSecond);

lastSetpoint = currentPose.getTranslation();

driveController.setTolerance(0.05);
thetaController.setTolerance(0.02);
</code></pre>
<p>}</p>
<p><a class="mention" href="/u/override">@Override</a><br>
public void execute() {<br>
running = true;</p>
<pre><code>// if (drive_kP.hasChanged(hashCode()) || turn_kP.hasChanged(hashCode())) {
// driveController.setP(drive_kP.get());
// thetaController.setP(turn_kP.get());
// }

Pose2d currentPose = drivetrain.getPose();
Pose2d targetPose = desiredPose.get();

double distance = currentPose.getTranslation().getDistance(targetPose.getTranslation());
double ffScaler =
    MathUtil.clamp(
        (distance - ff_minRadius) / (ff_maxRadius - ff_minRadius), 0.0, 1.0);
driveErrorAbs = distance;

driveController.reset(
    lastSetpoint.getDistance(targetPose.getTranslation()),
    driveController.getSetpoint().velocity);

double driveVelocityScalar =
    driveController.getSetpoint().velocity * ffScaler
        + driveController.calculate(driveErrorAbs, 0.0);

if (distance &lt; driveController.getPositionTolerance()) {
  driveVelocityScalar = 0.0;
}

lastSetpoint =
    new Pose2d(
            targetPose.getTranslation(),
            currentPose.getTranslation().minus(targetPose.getTranslation()).getAngle())
        .transformBy(GeomUtil.toTransform2d(driveController.getSetpoint().position, 0.0))
        .getTranslation();

double thetaVelocity =
    thetaController.getSetpoint().velocity * ffScaler
        + thetaController.calculate(
            currentPose.getRotation().getRadians(), targetPose.getRotation().getRadians());

double thetaErrorAbs =
    Math.abs(
        currentPose
            .getTranslation()
            .minus(targetPose.getTranslation())
            .getAngle()
            .getRadians());

if (thetaErrorAbs &lt; thetaController.getPositionTolerance()) {
  thetaVelocity = 0.0;
}

Translation2d driveVelocity =
    new Pose2d(
            new Translation2d(),
            currentPose.getTranslation().minus(targetPose.getTranslation()).getAngle())
        .transformBy(GeomUtil.toTransform2d(driveVelocityScalar, 0))
        .getTranslation();

// TODO: Test using 3.0
double linearSpeed = linearFF.get().getNorm() * 1.0;
double thetaSpeed = Math.abs(omegaFF.getAsDouble()) * 3.0;

driveVelocity =
    driveVelocity.interpolate(
        linearFF.get().times(Constants.DriveConstants.MAX_DRIVE_SPEED.magnitude()),
        linearSpeed);
thetaVelocity = MathUtil.interpolate(thetaVelocity, omegaFF.getAsDouble() * 0.5, thetaSpeed);

SwerveRequest.FieldCentricFacingAngle requestedVelocities = new SwerveRequest.FieldCentricFacingAngle().withHeadingPID(1, 0, 0).withDriveRequestType(DriveRequestType.Velocity);

double xSpeed = -driveVelocity.getX();
double ySpeed = -driveVelocity.getY();

double thetaTYLER = -thetaVelocity * 1;

drivetrain.setControl(requestedVelocities.
withVelocityX(xSpeed)
.withVelocityY(ySpeed)
.withTargetDirection(Rotation2d.fromDegrees(targetPose.getRotation().getDegrees()))
</code></pre>
<p>);</p>
<pre><code>SmartDashboard.putNumber("XAlignment Velocity", xSpeed);
SmartDashboard.putNumber("YAlignment Velocity", ySpeed);
SmartDashboard.putNumber("ThetaAlignment Velocity", thetaTYLER);
SmartDashboard.putNumber("x", currentPose.getX());
SmartDashboard.putNumber("Y", currentPose.getY());
SmartDashboard.putNumber("ROT", currentPose.getRotation().getDegrees());
SmartDashboard.putNumber("targetX", targetPose.getX());
SmartDashboard.putNumber("targetY", targetPose.getY());
SmartDashboard.putNumber("targetROT", targetPose.getRotation().getDegrees());
SmartDashboard.putNumber("absDriveError", driveErrorAbs);
SmartDashboard.putNumber("abdThetaError", thetaErrorAbs);
SmartDashboard.putNumber("errorX", currentPose.getX() - targetPose.getX());
SmartDashboard.putNumber("errorY", currentPose.getY() - targetPose.getY());
SmartDashboard.putNumber("errorROT", currentPose.getRotation().getDegrees() - targetPose.getRotation().getDegrees());
</code></pre>
<p>}</p>
<p><a class="mention" href="/u/override">@Override</a><br>
public void end(boolean interrupted) {<br>
drivetrain.applyRequest(() → new SwerveRequest.FieldCentric());<br>
running = false;<br>
drivetrain.setKillSwitch(true);<br>
}</p>
<p>public boolean atGoal() {<br>
return running &amp;&amp; driveController.atGoal() &amp;&amp; thetaController.atGoal();<br>
}</p>
<p>public boolean withinTolerance(double driveTolerance, Rotation2d thetaTolerance) {<br>
return running<br>
&amp;&amp; Math.abs(driveErrorAbs) &lt; driveTolerance<br>
&amp;&amp; Math.abs(thetaErrorAbs) &lt; thetaTolerance.getRadians();<br>
}</p>
<p><a class="mention" href="/u/override">@Override</a><br>
public boolean isFinished() {<br>
return atGoal();<br>
}<br>
}</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":2,"updated_at":"2025-03-08T02:07:21.476Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":52,"reads":69,"readers_count":68,"score":273.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":494697,"topic_slug":"help-with-aligning-to-a-pose-with-ctre-swerve","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":51272,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Waffler"},"post_url":"/t/help-with-aligning-to-a-pose-with-ctre-swerve/494697/1","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3550933,"name":"Kabir","username":"kn4","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/kn4/{size}/235296_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-08T02:57:12.840Z","cooked":"<p>It will be hard for people here to find the exact issue in so much code when you’re not entirely specific about what’s happening. With all the transformations that this class is doing, I would suspect there’s some coordinate system (robot-centric vs. field-centric) error going on. Have you accounted for the fact that FieldCentricFacingAngle uses the operator perspective for forward by default?</p>
<p>If you want to get this working, you should look at the telemetry you are putting to SmartDashboard and find out what part of the command is getting wrong numbers. I’ll quote a related post here:</p>
